before.enText: of a person or part of the body

data.enText: very thin so that the bones can be seen under the skin

data.chText: 由骨骼组成的；类似骨头的

tr: having bones especially many or prominent bones
very thin especially from disease or hunger or cold
example: a nightmare population of gaunt men and skeletal boys
kept life in his wasted frame only by grim concentration

value.def: Someone who has a bony face or bony hands, for example, has a very thin face or very thin hands, with very little flesh covering their bones.

example.ex: ...an old man with a bony face and white hair...
example.tran: 一位面部瘦削、头发花白的老者

example.ex: He poked a long bony finger in Billy's chest.
example.tran: 他用细长的手指捅了一下比利的胸口。

value.tran: 骨瘦如柴的；瘦骨嶙峋的

value.def: The bony parts of a person's or animal's body are the parts made of bone.

example.ex: ...the bony ridge of the eye socket.

value.def: If you describe fish that you are eating as bony, you mean that it has a lot of bones.
